# Room 12 Windows PowerShell

## Task 1 – Introduction

- PowerShell is the second command-line utility built for Windows, after cmd.exe.
- It combines a command-line shell, a scripting language, and a configuration management framework.
Learning objectives:
- Understand what PowerShell is and its capabilities.
- Learnt the basic structure of PowerShell’s language.
- Run basic PowerShell commands.
- Recognize PowerShell’s applications in cybersecurity.
- Prerequisites: completion of Windows and AD Fundamentals and Windows Command Line modules.

---

## Task 2 – What Is PowerShell

Definition
A cross-platform automation solution built on the .NET Framework.
Object-oriented, enabling manipulation of complex data and system components.
Available on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
Brief History
- Developed in the early 2000s to overcome cmd.exe and batch limitations.
- Designed by Jeffrey Snover with an object-oriented approach.
- Released in 2006, later expanded into PowerShell Core (2016, open-source, cross-platform).
Power of PowerShell
- Objects encapsulate properties (data) and methods (actions).
- Cmdlets return objects instead of plain text, allowing advanced manipulation.

