## Task 4 – Navigating the File System and Working with Files

- Get-ChildItem: lists files and directories.
- Set-Location: changes directory.
- New-Item: creates files or directories.
- Remove-Item: deletes files or directories.
- Copy-Item: copies files or directories.
- Move-Item: moves files or directories.
- Get-Content: displays file contents.

---

## Task 5 – Piping, Filtering, and Sorting Data 

Piping
- | passes objects between cmdlets.
Example:
powershell
- Get-ChildItem | Sort-Object Length
Filtering
- Where-Object: filters objects by conditions.
powershell
- Get-ChildItem | Where-Object {$_.Extension -eq ".txt"}
Comparison Operators
- -eq: equal to
- -ne: not equal
- -gt: greater than
- -ge: greater or equal
- -lt: less than
- -le: less or equal
- -like: matches a pattern
Refinement
- Select-Object: selects specific properties or limits results.
- Select-String: searches text patterns in files (supports regex).

---

## Task 6 – System and Network Information

- Get-ComputerInfo: retrieves full system details (OS, hardware, BIOS).
- Get-LocalUser: lists local user accounts.
- Get-NetIPConfiguration: shows network interface details.
- Get-NetIPAddress: lists all configured IP addresses.

---

## Task 7 – Real-Time System Analysis

- Get-Process: lists running processes with CPU/memory usage.
- Get-Service: shows service status (running, stopped, paused).
- Get-NetTCPConnection: displays active TCP connections.
- Get-FileHash: generates file hashes for integrity checks.
- Alternate Data Streams (ADS): reveals hidden NTFS streams attached to files.

---

## Task 8 – Scripting

- Scripting: writing and executing command sequences in text files to automate tasks.
- Benefits: saves time, reduces errors, handles complex tasks.
- Cybersecurity applications:
- Blue Team: log analysis, anomaly detection, IOC extraction, malware reverse engineering.
- Red Team: system enumeration, remote execution, obfuscated scripts for defense testing.
- Admins: automate integrity checks, enforce policies, monitor health, respond to incidents.
- Invoke-Command: executes commands/scripts on remote systems.
- Example: Invoke-Command -ScriptBlock { Get-Process } -ComputerName TargetPC

