## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Use Get-Help: always check documentation before running unfamiliar cmdlets.
- Test scripts safely: validate in controlled environments before production.
- Apply precise filters: avoid unnecessary data processing.
- Document scripts: maintain for reuse and audits.
- Monitor actively: use cmdlets to detect anomalies in processes, services, and connections.
- Ensure compatibility: distinguish between classic PowerShell and PowerShell Core.

